import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['home_score'], bins=11, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['home_score'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['home_score'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['home_score'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Home Scores')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of home scores?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['goal_difference'], bins=18, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.axvline(data['goal_difference'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    ax.axvline(data['goal_difference'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    ax.set_xlabel('Goal Difference')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of goal difference?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['division_count'] = 1
    division_counts = data.groupby('division').count()['division_count']
    division_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the most common division in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Division')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend([f'Most common division: {division_counts.idxmax()} ({division_counts.max():.2f})'])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    match_counts = data.groupby('date').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    plt.plot(match_counts['date'], match_counts['counts'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of matches over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Match Counts')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
